What. A. Weekend. 
I competed in my first Muay Thai tournament at the United States Muay Thai Open. I won my first bout and lost my second. 
.
I am humbled by this experience and grateful for the journey. After the Marines, I struggled to find myself. Muay Thai has given me something to work toward, focus, and much more.
.
I want to start by thanking my coaches @frlonewolf and @benledvina_coach 
Kru, your wisdom and knowledge are unmatched and I truly appreciate everything you’ve taught me. Wolfpack 🐺 for life. 
Ben, you run the best team/gym in the state and are truly an inspiration. Thank you for pushing me farther than I ever thought I could go. 
.
Thank you to all of my teammates and training partners from @southside_combatacademy 
You are all studs
.
Thank you to my Co-Worker/Partners/Friends over @gunfightercanyon for supporting me and pushing me to be better. 
.
Lastly, thank you to my wife @tori.mazzone for being there every step of the way. This wouldn’t be possible without you. 
.
Before Muay Thai, I was 230 pounds, struggling to find confidence, meaning, purpose, and more. All of these people are responsible for helping me find these things. I love you all.
HEART….SOMETHING YOU CAN’T TEACH AND WE HAVE IT!! 🐺🐺 #WeAreSouthsiders #usmto #muaythai #wolfpack #champchamp

Proud of my girls for collecting those belts!
Shoutout to @benledvina_coach and @southside_combatacademy for keeping us all killas!
Christmas 2023

I’ve made quite the transformation over the last few years. When I got out of the Marines, I weighed 239 pounds. Thanks to Muay Thai and constant pressure from my friends to stop being a fat shit, I am down to 165 pounds 💪

-M.S., CSM
-Gunfighter Canyon 
-USMC Veteran
-Father, Husband
@gunfightercanyon
